The paper describes a machine learning algorithm for generating and optimizing organic molecules, which involves exploring a synthesis graph and producing synthesizable candidates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer engineering (cs.CE), computer vision (cs.CV), and computational linguistics (cs.CL), as these sub-categories are relevant to the development of algorithms for data-driven optimization and modeling.
